 Nigeria youth international Valentine Ozornwafor has finally made his debut for Turkish giants Galatasaray two years since he signed for the Turkish giants. The 21-year old replaced experienced Dutch midfielder Ryan Donk in the 82nd minute of the match against Genclerbirligi. He wore jersey No 49. Last season, the left-footed central defender played on loan at ambitious Segunda Division side UD Almeria. Galatasaray won 6-0 at home and they are now just a point behind leaders and city rivals Besiktas. Post Views: 
